&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you an experienced Research Nurse looking for a career development or an experienced Band 7 looking for a change in direction?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;James Paget University Hospital is looking to recruit a forward thinking Band 7 Senior Clinical Research Nurse to manage the research delivery team of nurses, midwives and support staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role includes Direct Line Management, Study Support, Research Portfolio Management and Workforce Development. You will work closely with the Head of Research to deliver clinical research to high standards and also work in collaboration with the Clinical Research Network in the East of England.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will also be expected to be &#39;hands on&#39;, assessing and recruiting participants to research studies either in support of the team or your on your own study portfolio.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If research excites you and you want to play a part in the development of new therapies and treatments for future patients maybe this is the job for you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameKaren EadeJob titleHead of ResearchEmail addresskaren.eade@jpaget.nhs.ukTelephone number01493 453397&lt;/p&gt;
